WEBVTT

00:31.156 --> 00:31.990
Emily.

00:32.658 --> 00:33.492
Oh, shit!

00:41.542 --> 00:47.130
Is there any circumstance more terrifying
than when a child goes missing?

00:48.423 --> 00:52.594
By now, we all know the haunting stories
of Natalee Holloway...

00:52.594 --> 00:56.265
...the 18-year-old who vanished during
a trip to Aruba,

00:56.265 --> 00:57.891
and Gabby Petito,

00:58.559 --> 01:02.688
the young blogger whose remains
were eventually discovered in a park.

01:03.814 --> 01:06.942
The nation watched
around-the-clock coverage...

01:06.942 --> 01:07.860
OPD!

01:07.860 --> 01:10.195
...as every parent feared the worst.

01:10.779 --> 01:13.490
The same story is unfolding again.

01:13.490 --> 01:14.616
Emily Mills!

01:15.826 --> 01:22.165
Recently, a 16-year-old local teen
named Emily Mills disappeared.

01:22.833 --> 01:23.834
Sun.

01:26.253 --> 01:27.379
Hey. Hey.

01:30.632 --> 01:31.633
Okay.

01:36.513 --> 01:37.514
It's not her.

01:38.390 --> 01:43.145
But what if I told you another
local teen went missing a year ago?

01:43.729 --> 01:45.606
Her name is Drea Spivey.

01:46.273 --> 01:49.067
Drea's mother, Charise,
is a friend of mine.

01:49.568 --> 01:54.448
You haven't heard of Drea
because her story has never been covered

01:54.448 --> 01:57.326
by a single news outlet.

01:57.326 --> 02:00.078
Charise was finally able to find Drea

02:00.078 --> 02:02.623
by enlisting the help of friends
in the community.

02:03.415 --> 02:07.544
I interviewed this young girl
to better understand her story.

02:08.878 --> 02:11.465
But there's been an upsetting development.

02:12.382 --> 02:17.763
Sixteen-year-old Drea went missing again
almost 72 hours ago.

02:19.181 --> 02:23.227
With every hour that passes,
the hope to find Drea dims.

02:23.936 --> 02:25.020
This means...

02:26.313 --> 02:30.734
Charise is forced
to live that nightmare all over again.

02:37.199 --> 02:40.077
Just uploaded the podcast
to our new bosses at Boisterous.

02:43.872 --> 02:46.875
I never wanted to see Drea up here.

02:49.419 --> 02:53.924
Another in a sea of sweet, stolen faces.

02:53.924 --> 02:55.342
Drea makes 11 total.

02:55.342 --> 02:58.136
All reported missing
over the last four years in Oakland.

02:58.846 --> 03:01.431
But only one had come home to safety.

03:03.350 --> 03:04.643
Why run again?

03:05.602 --> 03:07.813
Okay. What's our next step?

03:09.189 --> 03:14.319
We conducted over 10 hours of interviews
with Drea before she went missing again.

03:16.613 --> 03:20.492
There must be something
in those recordings that could guide us.

03:29.626 --> 03:32.504
Drea, when the Capstones found you,

03:32.504 --> 03:35.757
you were in a drug den
and addicted to fentanyl.

03:37.176 --> 03:38.552
How did you end up there?

03:39.261 --> 03:41.096
This boy I met gave it to me.

03:41.096 --> 03:45.934
And the first time I snorted fentanyl,
I went somewhere else in my head.

03:46.602 --> 03:49.188
A door opened, I stepped through it,

03:49.188 --> 03:51.732
and everything
on the other side was different.

03:53.108 --> 03:57.070
I just sort of floated along,
and there was no more hurt.

03:58.906 --> 04:01.491
I kept doing it 'cause I wanted
to go wherever I wanted.

04:03.076 --> 04:04.077
Where would you go?

04:06.079 --> 04:07.331
Japanese Gardens.

04:08.332 --> 04:11.001
It's so green. I love it there.

04:12.252 --> 04:13.253
Why?

04:13.962 --> 04:16.673
I had my 11th birthday party there.

04:17.173 --> 04:20.928
That was probably the last time
I remember being legit happy.

04:21.970 --> 04:27.267
That was before my mom had problems
and I had to go into foster care.

04:29.144 --> 04:33.190
After a few years of foster homes,
I just started doing drugs.

04:33.815 --> 04:36.944
You've been sober now for six weeks.

04:38.028 --> 04:39.238
Do you get tempted?

04:40.197 --> 04:41.240
Oh, my God.

04:41.740 --> 04:44.660
Just the other day,
I ran into a friend from my trapping days.

04:45.160 --> 04:47.120
She told me she had
the High Hunter hookup.

04:48.330 --> 04:52.334
It would've been so easy to meet her.

04:53.710 --> 04:56.547
But I didn't.
-What is that? "High Hunter?"

04:57.130 --> 04:59.383
It's a-- It's just a new drug.

05:00.843 --> 05:02.594
But I thought about my life now,

05:03.762 --> 05:06.640
like all the little things
being one big reason to say no.

05:07.558 --> 05:08.934
So, I turned her down.

05:11.520 --> 05:13.397
I know that probably sounds hella corny.

05:17.734 --> 05:19.778
I think that sounds very brave.

05:21.822 --> 05:23.073
Good morning, Oakland.

05:23.073 --> 05:27.536
Three full days have passed since
Bay Area teen Emily Mills was last seen.

05:27.536 --> 05:30.080
Local police departments assured
Channel 13

05:30.080 --> 05:32.916
that bringing Emily home
is their top priority.

05:33.500 --> 05:35.419
The PTA meeting will begin shortly.

05:36.920 --> 05:38.422
Do you need me to get you something, baby?

05:38.422 --> 05:39.506
No. I'm good.

05:39.506 --> 05:40.883
You sure?
-Yeah.

05:40.883 --> 05:43.510
But you might need to step
in here if she doesn't get here soon.

05:44.094 --> 05:45.470
There might be a riot.

05:45.971 --> 05:47.514
How long is she gonna keep us waiting?

05:47.514 --> 05:50.893
She will be here any second.
Everyone, just settle down, please.

05:53.604 --> 05:57.441
I'm sorry. I was on the phone
with the superintendent,

05:57.441 --> 06:00.277
discussing protocol for
tomorrow night's Get Out The Vote event.

06:00.944 --> 06:04.239
Now, with all the cameras and people
on campus tomorrow,

06:04.239 --> 06:07.826
I wanted to have a conversation
about school safety.

06:09.536 --> 06:12.122
Two girls have gone missing
in the last few days,

06:13.457 --> 06:16.668
Emily Mills and Drea Spivey.

06:17.252 --> 06:19.588
Some of you may know
that Drea is a student--

06:20.714 --> 06:25.010
I hate to be indelicate,
but is this really a school safety issue?

06:26.595 --> 06:28.138
What are you saying, Mrs. Williams?

06:30.349 --> 06:31.934
Drea was a drug addict.

06:35.854 --> 06:37.564
What's Ashley's cell phone number?

06:37.564 --> 06:39.525
What does my daughter
have to do with this?

06:39.525 --> 06:43.195
You know what? It's okay.
I'll just message her.

06:43.779 --> 06:46.657
All I'm asking is what this has to do
with our kids.

06:46.657 --> 06:51.078
Our kids know not to do drugs
or whatever Drea was into.

06:54.289 --> 06:59.378
Done. I just messaged Ashley,
who should be in choir right about now.

07:00.254 --> 07:02.256
I pretended to be a boy from Bellarmine.

07:03.006 --> 07:04.216
I told her she was cute

07:04.716 --> 07:08.262
and to meet me in the gym if she wanted
to come to a hooky party.

07:08.262 --> 07:09.763
You can't do that.

07:09.763 --> 07:12.933
That's catfishing or something.

07:14.935 --> 07:19.064
We're using the gym right now, Ashley.
You can go back to choir. Thanks.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.444
In less than 45 seconds,

07:25.153 --> 07:28.991
I got your daughter,
who knows better than Drea,

07:30.576 --> 07:32.494
to meet a stranger in the gym.

07:34.746 --> 07:38.792
What happened to Drea could happen
to any one of your kids.

07:40.878 --> 07:42.212
Do you understand that?

07:44.673 --> 07:48.135
Lastly, I need volunteers
for tomorrow's event.

07:53.891 --> 07:54.892
Thank you.

07:58.312 --> 08:00.105
My parents are just inside.

08:00.105 --> 08:02.649
Don't worry.
That meeting will go on for hours.

08:03.150 --> 08:05.819
Yeah.
But if my dad catches us, he'll kill me.

08:06.820 --> 08:08.030
Or he'll just kill you--

08:08.864 --> 08:10.449
He'd make me watch.

08:13.535 --> 08:15.120
So, you really want me to stop?

08:16.121 --> 08:17.915
No, I wouldn't say that.

08:18.582 --> 08:20.000
Yeah.
-I just--

08:21.418 --> 08:23.378
I just wish we had some privacy.

08:25.756 --> 08:28.759
When can we go back to my cousins' house?
It's been a minute.

08:31.136 --> 08:32.136
Soon.

08:35.307 --> 08:36.308
Mrs. Killebrew.

08:36.892 --> 08:40.270
I was just keeping Trini
company during your meeting.

08:40.270 --> 08:41.438
Well, I'm here now.

08:41.438 --> 08:44.149
So, she doesn't need to be kept company
any longer, does she?

08:44.149 --> 08:45.234
Yes, ma'am.

08:46.818 --> 08:47.903
I'll text you.
-Yeah.

08:51.740 --> 08:53.200
You think I scared him?

08:53.200 --> 08:54.284
What?

08:54.284 --> 08:57.079
Your father always gets
to be the tough one. It's not fair.

08:58.747 --> 09:00.249
Wait, am I in trouble? Or...

09:00.249 --> 09:04.211
Sweetheart, if I told you all the places
that your grandmother caught me

09:04.211 --> 09:07.673
and my high school boyfriend hooking up,
you wouldn't look at me the same again.

09:07.673 --> 09:08.966
Mom.

09:08.966 --> 09:14.638
Trini, you're never in trouble
as long as you are honest with me, okay?

09:16.431 --> 09:18.183
All I care about is keeping you safe,

09:18.183 --> 09:20.853
especially with all
of this going on with Drea.

09:21.603 --> 09:23.438
And that is why you cannot be getting...

09:23.438 --> 09:24.940
Mom, I know.
-...into a stranger's car...

09:24.940 --> 09:27.651
I told you it was Aubrey's cousin.
-...and not answering your phone.

09:27.651 --> 09:29.152
You had us worried sick, honey.

09:30.571 --> 09:32.364
Yeah, I know.

09:32.364 --> 09:36.076
I'm sorry. I learned my lesson. Really.

09:37.619 --> 09:38.954
Well, then you have my trust.

09:43.000 --> 09:44.418
There's no way you're getting in.

09:44.418 --> 09:46.962
This is ludicrous. I know Detective Aames.

09:46.962 --> 09:48.422
Like you know Markus Killebrew?

09:49.006 --> 09:53.010
Yeah, how's he enjoying sleeping on piles
of our department's hard-earned cash?

09:55.846 --> 09:58.390
Finally. Aames, could you please
tell them to let me through?

09:58.390 --> 10:01.268
I thought I told you
you're not welcome here, Miss Parnell.

10:02.895 --> 10:04.354
It's Scoville.

10:04.354 --> 10:05.981
Take care of this, new guy.

10:05.981 --> 10:07.065
Time to go.

10:17.618 --> 10:20.621
Did we sell it?
-I think a little too well.

10:21.163 --> 10:22.873
Listen, I am sorry.

10:22.873 --> 10:25.709
I don't have any more news
on Drea Spivey. I am trying.

10:25.709 --> 10:28.504
No, they got you working Emily Mills
24 hours a day.

10:28.504 --> 10:29.588
You are not wrong.

10:30.088 --> 10:32.466
Well, if you can find an extra hour
in your day,

10:33.425 --> 10:35.636
something came up
in one of Drea's interviews.

10:35.636 --> 10:38.388
She made a reference to "High Hunter."

10:38.388 --> 10:39.848
Said it was a new drug.

10:40.390 --> 10:42.851
High Hunter? It's not one I've heard of.

10:42.851 --> 10:44.978
Well, if it isn't a drug,
what else could it be?

10:44.978 --> 10:47.272
It could be a dealer.
It could be a trap house.

10:47.272 --> 10:48.649
I'll look into it for you.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.486
Wait, is that--

10:52.986 --> 10:53.987
Andrew Finney.

10:53.987 --> 10:55.072
Andrew.
-Danny.

10:55.072 --> 10:57.908
Front-runner to be Oakland's next mayor.

10:57.908 --> 11:01.828
You wanna know why we're so pressed
to find Emily Mills? There's your answer.

11:04.331 --> 11:06.208
But he's not even in office yet.

11:06.208 --> 11:08.418
You beat that law-and-order
drum hard enough

11:08.418 --> 11:12.381
in the age of "defund police,"
you get a hero's welcome 'round here.

11:13.757 --> 11:15.217
Law and order for whom?

11:24.101 --> 11:25.102
Thank you.

11:27.729 --> 11:29.231
This guy's blowing up my phone.

11:29.982 --> 11:31.066
You like him?

11:31.066 --> 11:32.693
We had one date. We'll see.

11:34.945 --> 11:36.780
You should get back out there.

11:36.780 --> 11:37.948
That part.

11:37.948 --> 11:41.994
Tinder, BlackPeopleMeet,
Bumble, Hinge, JDate.

11:41.994 --> 11:44.454
JDate.
Get you a nice Jewish boy.

11:44.454 --> 11:45.998
All of it.

11:45.998 --> 11:47.249
I'm not using an app.

11:48.000 --> 11:51.628
Plus, I think I'm fine alone. For now.

11:53.338 --> 11:54.339
That's new.

11:54.965 --> 11:57.301
I mean, the old Poppy just had
to have herself some Ingram.

11:57.301 --> 11:59.928
Right? This new you is doing baller shit.

11:59.928 --> 12:02.639
Mrs. Rhoades would've never come up
with a stunt like this.

12:02.639 --> 12:05.142
What are you talking about?
I've always been this person.

12:06.977 --> 12:08.437
I have.

12:09.605 --> 12:12.816
Remember when Uncle Bug
brought me over to Aunt Leona's

12:12.816 --> 12:16.153
and I had us crash that
little bougie tea party she used to hold

12:16.153 --> 12:18.405
in the backyard?
-I forgot all about that.

12:18.405 --> 12:22.534
It was sponsored by the Links, and we
weren't allowed to come and get any cake.

12:22.534 --> 12:26.079
We sure did make a ruckus when we came
in there banging them pots and pans.

12:26.079 --> 12:29.458
We made an impact. Aunt Leona was pissed.

12:29.458 --> 12:32.920
Why is she insisting that we go back
to that house to pick up Mom's stuff?

12:32.920 --> 12:35.923
I just hate the idea of going back
to that place. Too many bad memories.

12:35.923 --> 12:38.509
Yeah, it has a lot of bad memories
for me too.

12:39.218 --> 12:44.223
Not because I lived there,
but 'cause Aunt Leona shut me out.

12:44.806 --> 12:47.392
Let's just get it over with then,
so we all can move on.

12:48.769 --> 12:50.145
That heifer's moving to Vineyard,

12:50.145 --> 12:52.189
so it's good riddance.
-Well...

12:52.189 --> 12:54.608
All the way around.

12:54.608 --> 12:56.944
Cheers on that. Goodbye.
-Yes.

13:03.033 --> 13:05.619
Hey.

13:07.871 --> 13:08.956
What do you think?

13:12.209 --> 13:13.210
It's perfect.

13:20.509 --> 13:24.638
I can't stay long. I'm meeting with some
of the other MCs, let 'em know about Drea.

13:25.138 --> 13:27.516
Have you ever heard of High Hunter?

13:28.225 --> 13:29.226
No, what's that?

13:29.810 --> 13:31.520
It's a drug Drea mentioned.

13:32.145 --> 13:35.732
I'm just trying to figure out what it is
and where she used to get it.

13:37.276 --> 13:38.777
I'll keep my ears to the ground.

13:39.278 --> 13:41.280
Aames didn't know anything.

13:41.280 --> 13:43.365
He knows OPD ain't doing enough.

13:43.907 --> 13:45.784
This is something we can handle ourselves.

13:45.784 --> 13:47.119
Daddy--
-I mean it!

13:58.714 --> 13:59.715
Daddy...

14:01.550 --> 14:04.136
are you sure it's okay for me
to stay in this house?

14:04.136 --> 14:05.053
I--

14:05.846 --> 14:09.183
I said my name is Poppy Scoville
on my podcast. I--

14:10.767 --> 14:13.187
You don't need my approval to stay.
-I know.

14:16.690 --> 14:17.691
I'm just...

14:19.651 --> 14:23.113
trying to figure out
what my declaration really means.

14:25.741 --> 14:28.493
Is that why you wanna do the podcast
on Drea and the missing girls?

14:28.493 --> 14:29.912
So you can prove yourself.

14:31.413 --> 14:32.414
Maybe.

14:33.540 --> 14:35.584
Maybe to redeem myself too.

14:37.836 --> 14:42.508
I think of those girls, I think how easily
I could have been one of 'em.

14:42.508 --> 14:43.800
Yeah, but you're here.

14:44.635 --> 14:46.345
You're Poppy Scoville.

14:47.596 --> 14:50.140
And being a Scoville has nothing to do
with geography.

14:50.140 --> 14:51.975
It's about how you carry yourself.

14:56.605 --> 14:57.606
Keep your head up.

14:59.107 --> 15:00.192
We got work to do.

15:07.574 --> 15:11.453
I'm outside the Piedmont home
of missing teen Emily Mills.

15:11.453 --> 15:15.624
Following Emily's story
is mayoral candidate Andrew Finney.

15:15.624 --> 15:17.209
It's a horrible situation.

15:18.168 --> 15:19.753
Every parent's worst nightmare.

15:20.337 --> 15:23.131
The crime in this city
has gotten out of control.

15:31.640 --> 15:35.644
Good afternoon,
community members, stakeholders and press.

15:36.228 --> 15:38.689
I'm Lee Hackman,
and this is my wife Sybil.

15:41.149 --> 15:45.654
We started our company, Questeur,
out of a garage

15:45.654 --> 15:47.948
when we were across the bay, at Stanford.

15:48.824 --> 15:53.120
And today, Questeur is one of
the largest tech companies in the world.

15:53.120 --> 15:57.207
And we're about to break ground on our
new Questeur campus right here in Oakland.

15:57.207 --> 15:59.376
That better mean jobs for the community.

16:01.879 --> 16:02.880
You bet.

16:04.715 --> 16:08.218
We owe a huge thank you
to Oak Creek High School

16:08.218 --> 16:09.720
for lending us their campus.

16:10.429 --> 16:11.805
Over the past seven years,

16:11.805 --> 16:15.934
this school has become one
of the top performing schools in Oakland.

16:16.894 --> 16:20.731
In other words, we know where to keep
an eye out for future Questeur employees.

16:21.899 --> 16:24.610
Superintendent Lennon, please stand up,

16:24.610 --> 16:27.571
so that we can acknowledge you
and all that you've done here.

16:28.864 --> 16:29.865
All that he's done?

16:30.449 --> 16:32.951
Just smile. I'll key his car later.

16:32.951 --> 16:36.079
Most of you already have
the Questeur messaging app.

16:36.079 --> 16:38.832
But we've recently added a new feature

16:38.832 --> 16:42.085
that enables anyone
to easily register to vote.

16:42.085 --> 16:43.420
And for today only,

16:43.420 --> 16:47.591
you can use the app to submit questions
directly to the candidates,

16:47.591 --> 16:48.884
which I recommend you do.

16:48.884 --> 16:51.970
Oakland is in a period of transition.

16:51.970 --> 16:56.517
So now, more than ever, it's critical
that we vote as informed citizens.

16:56.517 --> 16:58.227
So without further ado,

16:58.227 --> 17:03.065
please welcome Rachel McKegney,
Everett Hoagland and Andrew Finney.

17:06.527 --> 17:10.571
They are our future,
and we need to invest in them accordingly.

17:10.571 --> 17:13.200
While in office, I championed Measure W.

17:13.992 --> 17:17.829
By utilizing funds allocated
in this anti-gang initiative,

17:17.829 --> 17:20.874
police can focus
on specific areas of the city.

17:20.874 --> 17:25.587
And if elected, I intend to reduce
the budget for local law enforcement.

17:25.587 --> 17:28.089
So I urge you to vote for me.

17:29.341 --> 17:30.342
There's abs--

17:33.595 --> 17:36.849
There's absolutely no reason why
a progressive candidate can't

17:36.849 --> 17:38.934
also support a strong police department.

17:38.934 --> 17:41.270
Please pardon the interruption.

17:42.437 --> 17:48.777
The faces you see before you
are all missing girls from Oakland,

17:49.361 --> 17:51.363
with families who want them home.

17:52.114 --> 17:55.242
This is Drea Spivey,

17:56.201 --> 17:58.328
a student at this very school,

17:58.328 --> 18:00.914
who went missing almost four days ago,

18:00.914 --> 18:04.793
but the search party
for her had very little police support.

18:05.502 --> 18:07.379
We came to ask why.

18:08.547 --> 18:09.548
Why?

18:10.799 --> 18:12.676
Does this girl not deserve attention?

18:13.802 --> 18:18.307
Is it not imperative
to allocate resources to help find her?

18:20.184 --> 18:26.231
If you feel as we do, we need you
to put pressure on the police department

18:26.231 --> 18:29.526
and the news media
to bring these girls home.

18:29.526 --> 18:33.906
Bring our girls home!
-Yes, bring 'em back.

18:33.906 --> 18:35.699
Bring all of them home.

18:35.699 --> 18:36.783
Yes.

18:36.783 --> 18:39.661
Bring our girls home!
They need to be with us!

18:39.661 --> 18:43.999
I've heard a lot of people talking
about Emily Mills.

18:45.792 --> 18:49.880
I hope they find her safe,
so she can be returned to her family.

18:53.675 --> 18:55.594
But my daughter is missing too.

18:57.679 --> 18:59.848
My Drea matters too.

19:00.557 --> 19:04.811
She's my only child,
and I need you to help me find her.

19:04.811 --> 19:06.730
Bring her home.
-Bring 'em home.

19:06.730 --> 19:08.899
Do something!
-Your daughter does matter.

19:10.901 --> 19:14.154
And I hope she's home with you soon.
Your questions are good ones.

19:14.863 --> 19:17.324
But there is a time and a place
for all our words.

19:18.742 --> 19:20.661
Say her name!
-Say her name!

19:21.954 --> 19:24.456
Say her name!
-Say her name!

19:24.456 --> 19:29.294
Say her name! Say her name! Say her name!

19:29.294 --> 19:38.846
Say her name! Say her name!

19:38.846 --> 19:40.639
Say her name!

19:49.606 --> 19:51.149
That was some stunt.

19:53.569 --> 19:57.281
