that this was foisted upon you,

19:57.281 --> 19:59.700
but to embarrass your school,
your students

19:59.700 --> 20:03.412
and your boss this way
makes me question your judgment entirely.

20:04.705 --> 20:07.040
If you continue
to act like one of the school's children,

20:07.040 --> 20:09.168
I will have no choice
but to treat you like one.

20:11.545 --> 20:12.713
I'll do better.

20:22.014 --> 20:23.849
I hope I didn't get you into trouble.

20:23.849 --> 20:25.225
Only the good kind.

20:25.976 --> 20:27.769
Eva Pierre.
-Poppy Scoville.

20:28.270 --> 20:30.230
Markus Killebrew told me all about you.

20:31.315 --> 20:33.442
You think that demonstration is
gonna make a difference?

20:33.442 --> 20:34.818
I don't know.

20:34.818 --> 20:39.907
Right now, I'd just settle for action.
Police, political, tweets, whatever.

20:40.532 --> 20:42.201
It's what all these girls deserve.

20:42.201 --> 20:43.285
Yeah.

20:44.203 --> 20:45.412
We can hope.

20:45.913 --> 20:46.914
Miss Pierre?

20:47.706 --> 20:51.001
Poppy, this is Tanya,
one of Drea's friends.

20:51.877 --> 20:53.837
Nice to meet you, Tanya.
-You too.

20:53.837 --> 20:57.466
I saw what you did in there. I wanna help.
I ju-- I'm just not sure how.

20:58.091 --> 21:01.803
Well, have you ever heard
Drea mention someone

21:01.803 --> 21:03.472
with the nickname "High Hunter"?

21:04.598 --> 21:06.433
Could that be her drug dealer maybe?

21:07.809 --> 21:10.229
I don't know anything about him.
I don't use.

21:10.938 --> 21:13.065
I should go.
I have a lot of homework to do.

21:13.065 --> 21:14.483
I think it can wait.

21:15.108 --> 21:17.152
I don't think you're being honest
with me, Tanya.

21:18.070 --> 21:19.404
That's very disappointing.

21:22.241 --> 21:25.118
She hasn't texted me in a week.
I'm scared.

21:25.786 --> 21:28.497
Give me your fear. Let us act on it.

21:32.876 --> 21:34.837
I never heard her call him High Hunter,

21:34.837 --> 21:38.090
but Drea did have
this guy she was hanging around with.

21:38.090 --> 21:39.424
Do you know his name?

21:40.551 --> 21:42.135
All I know is that he was older,

21:42.135 --> 21:44.388
and that Drea said
that he took care of her.

21:45.222 --> 21:47.099
But you didn't like the sound of him?

21:48.141 --> 21:49.142
She seemed scared.

21:50.644 --> 21:52.855
Everything she described sounded
real controlling.

21:53.897 --> 21:55.774
The last few weeks, she kept telling me

21:55.774 --> 21:57.776
that she needed some time
in her happy place.

21:59.278 --> 22:01.238
That's all I know. I swear.

22:01.238 --> 22:03.323
It's okay. You can go, Tanya. Thank you.

22:03.824 --> 22:04.825
Thanks.

22:07.077 --> 22:11.540
I hate to be the one to bring this up,
but have you considered that--

22:11.540 --> 22:13.750
This controlling guy is Drea's pimp?

22:15.961 --> 22:17.713
I'm trying not to go there.

22:18.297 --> 22:19.298
But...

22:22.509 --> 22:25.470
I think I know
where Drea's happy place is.

22:28.932 --> 22:30.726
You look good doing the dishes.

22:30.726 --> 22:32.477
I look good doing a lot of things.

22:33.687 --> 22:34.897
Hey, baby?
-Uh-huh.

22:34.897 --> 22:36.899
Let me ask you a question.

22:36.899 --> 22:39.902
You think that Trini and Aubrey are--

22:41.278 --> 22:43.363
Jesus Christ, I can't even say it.

22:45.032 --> 22:46.617
No. Trini told me she's a virgin.

22:47.409 --> 22:48.911
So you two talked about it?

22:49.536 --> 22:52.164
Don't look so shocked.
We talk about a lot of things.

22:53.665 --> 22:55.501
How come you never told me about it?

22:55.501 --> 22:57.419
You never asked before.

22:57.419 --> 23:00.923
And seeing as how you--
You can't even say it,

23:01.548 --> 23:04.635
I was right in assuming it's a don't ask,
don't tell policy.

23:05.469 --> 23:06.553
Damn.

23:06.553 --> 23:09.723
So I guess we have to invite
that knucklehead over for dinner, huh?

23:10.599 --> 23:13.852
Look, I just want to sit the boy down,
look him right in his eyes.

23:13.852 --> 23:15.270
See what he's all about.

23:15.270 --> 23:16.355
Okay.

23:16.897 --> 23:20.692
You wanna broach that subject
with Trini, by all means, go ahead.

23:20.692 --> 23:21.777
I will.

23:22.402 --> 23:25.656
And I won't even be nice about it either.
-Okay, big man.

23:25.656 --> 23:26.782
Excuse me.

23:26.782 --> 23:28.534
I gotta go to work.
-Uh-huh.

23:29.201 --> 23:30.744
Love you.
-I love you, baby.

23:30.744 --> 23:32.246
Bring me back something sweet?

23:32.246 --> 23:33.330
Yes, I will.

23:34.289 --> 23:35.582
It'll be me.

23:39.962 --> 23:40.963
That's--

23:41.922 --> 23:42.923
Hi, sir.

23:44.007 --> 23:46.718
Where are you racing off to,
urgent meeting of the assholes?

23:47.719 --> 23:48.720
What?

23:51.849 --> 23:53.058
Just wondering,

23:54.184 --> 23:58.063
how someone
with your temperament became a principal.

23:59.523 --> 24:01.483
I don't need them to like me.

24:01.483 --> 24:03.026
They need me to protect them.

24:03.861 --> 24:06.655
That's what my high school principal did
for me.

24:10.534 --> 24:12.452
My mom was illegal.

24:14.288 --> 24:16.832
She brought me here from Haiti
for a shot at a better education,

24:16.832 --> 24:21.295
but was deported
while I was still in high school.

24:22.880 --> 24:24.673
I didn't have anybody looking out for me.

24:25.299 --> 24:27.801
My high school principal, Evelyn Varga,

24:27.801 --> 24:30.179
she made sure
that school was a safe place, you know?

24:30.179 --> 24:32.514
Like a refuge for me.

24:33.807 --> 24:35.559
She made sure I graduated on time,

24:35.559 --> 24:38.645
and I was the first one in my family
to go to college.

24:40.814 --> 24:41.815
Here I am.

24:43.192 --> 24:44.902
Your mother must be so proud.

24:45.694 --> 24:48.071
You honor her sacrifice every day.

24:50.282 --> 24:53.202
She passed away
shortly after being deported.

24:54.870 --> 24:56.079
I was barely 20.

24:58.498 --> 25:00.584
I lost my mother too young as well.

25:01.084 --> 25:02.461
Isn't it always too young?

25:14.056 --> 25:16.475
Hi, we're looking for a missing girl.
-Thank you.

25:16.475 --> 25:17.559
Take a look.

25:25.859 --> 25:28.487
Excuse me, have you seen that girl?

25:31.448 --> 25:32.449
Nah.

25:58.976 --> 26:02.229
You'll have to stop blaming yourself
for Drea going missing again.

26:03.021 --> 26:04.982
It's not on you or the Capstones.

26:06.817 --> 26:09.069
I've been thinking
about a lot of things, Lil.

26:10.279 --> 26:11.780
My legacy--
-Is secure.

26:11.780 --> 26:12.948
Is it?

26:13.824 --> 26:15.284
What are you talking about?

26:22.249 --> 26:25.586
OPD put out a list
of calls they gonna stop responding to.

26:26.086 --> 26:30.132
Basically, 10 commandments that all say,
"Fuck you, deal with it yourself."

26:30.132 --> 26:33.010
So, I been thinking I will.

26:34.052 --> 26:35.929
You got nothing to prove to anyone.

26:37.222 --> 26:39.349
Said the same thing to Poppy.

26:40.267 --> 26:43.896
I'm happy y'all two have gotten
so much closer the last couple of months.

26:44.479 --> 26:45.898
I can see it's good for you.

26:46.815 --> 26:47.858
She's still lost.

26:48.525 --> 26:50.194
And my grandma used to say,

26:50.194 --> 26:53.113
"There always gonna be some people
who are just a little bit restless."

26:53.614 --> 26:55.616
Georgia grandmas know everything.
-Yeah.

26:58.035 --> 27:01.705
You got a call today from Andrew Finney.

27:03.415 --> 27:04.833
The cat running for mayor?

27:06.210 --> 27:07.794
Said he wants to meet with you.

27:08.462 --> 27:12.049
Could be he saw the influence
that you have and wants to work with you.

27:14.009 --> 27:15.177
With our history?

27:16.303 --> 27:18.013
Capstones don't do politics.

27:18.514 --> 27:20.224
Well, maybe they should.

27:27.397 --> 27:30.234
Why did you fall in love with me?

27:32.653 --> 27:36.406
Because there's no one else
in the world like you.

27:37.658 --> 27:41.119
Nothing you do will make you more
of a man than you already are.

27:42.204 --> 27:46.166
You're the most compassionate,
authentic soul I've ever met.

27:47.084 --> 27:51.129
And I've loved you from the inside out.

27:51.713 --> 27:52.714
Always.

27:54.216 --> 27:55.509
Inside out, huh?

28:16.572 --> 28:20.033
Have you seen the latest dispatch
from our new overlords at Boisterous?

28:20.951 --> 28:22.703
Do they have a problem with our VO sample?

28:22.703 --> 28:27.541
No, but they'd just love us to lean
into the "tragic nature of Drea's life."

28:28.709 --> 28:29.710
Look, Noa...

28:31.253 --> 28:33.005
I think Drea is being trafficked.

28:37.593 --> 28:39.553
They're gonna hang Drea
and Charise out to dry.

28:39.553 --> 28:43.849
I will control it, okay?
I know how to handle Boisterous.

28:43.849 --> 28:48.312
It may mean a lot of haggling with
corporate, but I can handle Boisterous.

28:48.312 --> 28:51.523
We are going to have to be able
to do the story we wanna do.

28:51.523 --> 28:53.692
These guys are asking
for sensationalist chum.

28:53.692 --> 28:56.653
And we may not feel it at first,
but it'll be a picture here

28:56.653 --> 28:58.322
and a sound bite there,
and before we know it,

28:58.322 --> 29:00.199
the marketing will start
to drive the narrative.

29:00.199 --> 29:02.367
It's how Micah lost sight
of who she really was.

29:02.367 --> 29:03.327
Okay.

29:03.827 --> 29:04.745
Okay.

29:05.245 --> 29:06.455
I'll call the lawyers.

29:06.455 --> 29:09.208
See if they can amend the contract
to give us marketing approval.

29:09.708 --> 29:10.709
Thank you.

29:13.212 --> 29:14.213
Okay.

29:33.106 --> 29:34.107
Use your legs.

29:35.317 --> 29:36.860
Use your legs.

29:40.030 --> 29:41.615
Okay, okay. Enough.

29:50.332 --> 29:52.292
What happened at the Gardens with Poppy?

29:52.292 --> 29:54.127
I haven't seen you like this in years.

29:54.628 --> 29:55.838
You think she's good people?

29:56.880 --> 29:58.382
You're the one that talked to her.

29:58.382 --> 30:01.552
Yeah, she's not how I expected her to be.

30:03.011 --> 30:04.137
And don't forget cute.

30:05.264 --> 30:06.682
This man's not blind.

30:08.851 --> 30:12.604
So what, you're thinking about working
with her or something?

30:13.647 --> 30:14.773
I can't do this alone.

30:16.608 --> 30:17.609
Just be careful

30:18.861 --> 30:21.196
because that's a fucking live wire
right there.

30:22.489 --> 30:23.490
So am I.

30:24.199 --> 30:25.242
Let's go. Come on. Again.

30:25.242 --> 30:27.077
Let's go, old man.

30:27.077 --> 30:28.537
Shake a leg.
-All right.

30:46.263 --> 30:47.264
Hello?

30:49.183 --> 30:50.225
Hello?

30:51.018 --> 30:53.103
You have to stop looking for me.

30:54.062 --> 30:55.063
Drea?

30:55.063 --> 30:56.398
I'm fine.

30:56.398 --> 30:58.400
So, why don't you come home?

30:58.400 --> 31:01.278
We all miss you and want you safe.

31:02.196 --> 31:03.572
What's going on, honey?

31:03.572 --> 31:04.865
You wouldn't understand.

31:05.782 --> 31:08.744
Well, does it have anything to do
with that guy Tanya mentioned?

31:12.706 --> 31:13.916
I owe him.

31:13.916 --> 31:15.000
How much?

31:15.000 --> 31:19.213
Whatever it is,
we can pay off your debt to High Hunter.

31:19.838 --> 31:20.839
What?

31:22.132 --> 31:23.342
It's not that simple.

31:23.967 --> 31:29.181
Look, he's done so much for me,
so now I have to return the favor.

31:30.140 --> 31:31.141
What does that mean?

31:33.227 --> 31:34.228
I don't know.

31:35.103 --> 31:37.105
Give guys blow jobs and stuff.

31:38.398 --> 31:42.653
Drea, that man is pimping you out.

31:46.949 --> 31:48.116
Drea?

31:48.116 --> 31:49.618
Don't tell my mom.

31:49.618 --> 31:51.537
She loves you so much.

31:51.537 --> 31:53.121
She'd do anything for you.

31:54.122 --> 31:55.916
Can that guy you're with say that?

31:57.459 --> 31:59.503
I got this, okay?

32:00.254 --> 32:01.255
Tell my mom that.

32:01.255 --> 32:07.052
Okay, can you at least call her
and let her know you're alive?

32:08.345 --> 32:09.346
Okay?

32:17.938 --> 32:18.939
Trafficked?

32:23.110 --> 32:24.278
How did this happen?

32:25.654 --> 32:28.156
Could you tell where she was?
Did you hear anything?

32:28.699 --> 32:29.700
No.

32:30.409 --> 32:33.453
But it's not too late for her, Charise.
We can still bring her home.

32:33.954 --> 32:35.747
Look, Poppy's right, okay?

32:36.456 --> 32:38.917
Now, Drea wouldn't even had called her

32:38.917 --> 32:41.044
if some part of her
didn't wanna come home.

32:42.337 --> 32:44.131
My question for you is,

32:45.424 --> 32:47.634
do you want me putting this
on the podcast?

32:48.802 --> 32:51.221
When you agreed
to let me interview her initially,

32:51.221 --> 32:54.474
it was a talk about her time missing
and the drugs.

32:55.142 --> 32:56.977
But this is different.

32:57.561 --> 32:58.770
It's up to you.

33:00.189 --> 33:02.274
I won't air anything you don't want me to.

33:10.741 --> 33:13.702
If you think it has a chance
to bring her home...

33:16.580 --> 33:17.581
do it.

33:33.096 --> 33:35.557
Hey.

33:38.310 --> 33:39.311
So...

33:40.437 --> 33:43.857
Charise approved using Drea's interviews
to talk about trafficking.

33:44.441 --> 33:46.401
What'd the lawyer say
about amending the contract?

33:47.903 --> 33:49.029
Yeah, she said,

33:49.821 --> 33:54.618
"Boisterous is open
to discussion regarding marketing."

33:54.618 --> 33:57.120
Pop, they'll use the most lurid details.

33:57.120 --> 33:58.705
The campaign will be all about sex,

33:58.705 --> 34:01.041
and the girls will be a footnote.
-Not if we find them.

34:01.041 --> 34:04.378
Have you seen the advertising
for their women's prison podcast?

34:04.378 --> 34:07.714
Every female inmate wears
the tightest tank top imaginable.

34:07.714 --> 34:09.842
But that's not gonna happen
with Reconsidered.

34:09.842 --> 34:13.637
Maybe not, but doesn't it bother you
that it's the Boisterous MO?

34:14.304 --> 34:18.266
Sure, but these girls' story is way
too important,

34:18.266 --> 34:21.853
so, I'll give the tank tops an eye roll

34:21.853 --> 34:25.148
and keep it moving if it means
our message gets out to the masses.

34:25.148 --> 34:28.652
We're not even ready to go on air
with a trafficking episode.

34:28.652 --> 34:31.280
This pivot requires more research.
We need more time.

34:31.280 --> 34:32.614
Drea doesn't have time!

34:32.614 --> 34:35.199
We're already compromising.
Can't you see that?

34:35.199 --> 34:37.953
What I see is an opportunity to help.

34:37.953 --> 34:39.746
Look, when I was with Alex,

34:39.746 --> 34:42.373
I saw how
our podcast affected his daughter.

34:43.166 --> 34:45.752
She heard every word other kids said
about her,

34:45.752 --> 34:49.590
and that was without salacious marketing
and sensationalized copy.

34:49.590 --> 34:51.967
If we do things the Boisterous way,

34:53.135 --> 34:56.722
Drea and the other girls will be hurt
much more than Alex's daughter.

34:56.722 --> 34:57.806
What are you saying?

34:57.806 --> 35:00.976
The message doesn't matter if
this is how we're gonna convey it.

35:00.976 --> 35:03.520
I wish you would just trust me!

35:04.021 --> 35:05.647
I wish you would trust me!
I'm telling you,

35:05.647 --> 35:10.694
I am not gonna let Boisterous exploit
Charise, Drea or any of the girls.

35:10.694 --> 35:12.070
I'm not, Noa.

35:15.240 --> 35:18.452
Poppy, I just--

35:21.455 --> 35:24.917
I just don't think that I'm compatible
with Boisterous.

35:27.669 --> 35:30.214
So, this'll be my last podcast.

35:34.426 --> 35:35.677
As a journalist,

35:36.303 --> 35:41.266
when I came across something horrific,
something I wanted to turn away from,

35:42.434 --> 35:45.812
I couldn't. I had to confront it.

35:47.147 --> 35:50.400
So, here it goes.

35:52.444 --> 35:56.990
Drea Spivey is a bright,
beautiful young woman.

35:58.408 --> 36:01.161
She's a junior
at Oak Creek High in Oakland.

36:01.703 --> 36:07.167
Her favorite subject is biology,
and her dream is to become a nurse.

36:08.460 --> 36:12.005
And she is also a victim
of sex trafficking.

36:13.507 --> 36:15.175
When people think of sex trafficking,

36:15.175 --> 36:19.513
their minds go
to scary men kidnapping girls

36:19.513 --> 36:21.265
and taking them across borders.

36:23.350 --> 36:29.356
But sex trafficking is more often
a neighbor, a friend,

36:30.691 --> 36:36.196
even someone on social media
who lures kids into trusting them,

36:36.196 --> 36:39.241
only to turn around and abuse them.

36:40.951 --> 36:43.620
People always assume
this could never happen to them

36:43.620 --> 36:44.705
or their kids.

36:46.540 --> 36:50.002
But the truth is, it is happening.

36:50.711 --> 36:55.674
And not just in some shadowy,
forgotten corner of the hood.

36:57.009 --> 37:01.138
It's happening in our schools,
our community.

37:02.014 --> 37:05.309
Trafficking has been labeled an epidemic
in Oakland.

37:07.019 --> 37:09.813
How much we are to blame
for our negligence

37:10.522 --> 37:13.442
is a conversation for you...

37:15.694 --> 37:16.904
and the god you worship.

37:18.030 --> 37:19.281
What you looking for, mama?

37:19.281 --> 37:20.365
Get in.

37:23.327 --> 37:24.578
I know one thing:

37:26.330 --> 37:29.875
Drea and the other missing girls like her,

37:29.875 --> 37:31.376
wherever they are,

37:32.711 --> 37:34.129
deserve our love.

37:36.131 --> 37:38.550
I don't got track marks.
I don't mess with that shit.

37:39.760 --> 37:41.053
Smart girl.

37:41.053 --> 37:42.304
I aim to find them

37:42.971 --> 37:45.849
and the people responsible
for taking them away.

37:47.017 --> 37:50.145
Sex trafficking is a cancer on our city.

37:51.605 --> 37:53.565
I know I can't cure it.

37:54.900 --> 37:56.568
But I can expose it.

37:57.236 --> 37:59.947
I hope you'll follow me into this world,

38:01.573 --> 38:02.991
however dark it may be.

38:05.911 --> 38:07.704
My name is Poppy Scoville,

38:09.665 --> 38:13.627
and I'd like you to reconsider.

38:28.058 --> 38:30.394
I'll clean this up and send it to ya.

38:30.394 --> 38:34.606
I may lay a little music over the end,
but it'll be ready to air tomorrow.

38:35.148 --> 38:36.400
Sounds good.
-Yeah.

38:36.400 --> 38:37.484
Thank you.
-Sure.

38:42.990 --> 38:46.743
I was gonna give this to you when we got
to 50 million listeners,

38:46.743 --> 38:49.580
but you'll be there soon enough.

38:51.373 --> 38:52.499
Thank you.

38:56.170 --> 38:57.296
It's been an honor.

38:58.338 --> 38:59.339
Me too.
-Yeah.

39:06.263 --> 39:07.598
Nothing new under the sun.

39:08.557 --> 39:10.225
But there are new suns.
-Yeah.

39:25.407 --> 39:26.533
Is that...

39:31.038 --> 39:32.789
"To my favorite Oakland girl.

39:33.540 --> 39:37.461
Now that you have your roots,
may you never lose your voice.

39:38.295 --> 39:40.380
Love, Noa."

39:50.766 --> 39:51.767
Hey, Aames.

39:56.480 --> 39:57.481
Wait, what?

40:31.098 --> 40:32.224
Hold up, guys.

40:55.831 --> 40:56.832
Thank you.

41:29.948 --> 41:31.658
I don't want this to be real.

41:38.999 --> 41:40.584
This motel's on High Street.

41:42.294 --> 41:43.670
Guess what the nickname is.

41:45.506 --> 41:46.965
High Hunter.

41:50.385 --> 41:52.471
Somebody wanted to shut her up, Aames.

41:55.307 --> 41:56.683
I'm gonna find out who.
